A basic outline for how to install PEBIL.

1. System Requirements
Operating System        Linux
Binary Format           Elf
Architecture            X86 or X86_64

2. Add the following to your shell login script (assuming the installation is
at /path/to/pebil/)

bash (64bit example):
PEBIL_ROOT=${HOME}/PEBIL
PEBIL_LIB=${PEBIL_ROOT}/lib
PEBIL_BIN=${PEBIL_ROOT}/bin
PEBIL_LD_FLAGS="-Wl,--hash-style=sysv"
PEBIL_GFORT=gfortran
IAPI_PLATFORM=x86_64-unknown-linux2.4
PATH=${PATH}:${PEBIL_BIN}
export PEBIL_ROOT
export PEBIL_LIB
export PEBIL_BIN
export PEBIL_LD_FLAGS
export PEBIL_GFORT
export IAPI_PLATFORM
export PATH

csh (32bit example):
setenv PEBIL_ROOT /path/to/pebil/
setenv PEBIL_LIB ${PEBIL_ROOT}/lib
setenv PEBIL_BIN ${PEBIL_ROOT}/bin
setenv PEBIL_LD_FLAGS "-Wl,--hash-style=sysv"
setenv PEBIL_GFORT gfortran
setenv IAPI_PLATFORM i386-unknown-linux2.4
setenv PATH ${PATH}:${PEBIL_BIN}

NOTE: if you get a build error/warning saying that your compiler doesn't 
recognize the argument --hash-style, your compiler is likely already using 
sysv-style tables and you can entirely disregard the PEBIL_LD_FLAGS 
variable.

3. build 
   A. build the udis86 library. go to external/udis86 and see the README within
   for details

run `gmake' from the top-level directory

4. run
Details on how to run:
pebil --help

Examples:
pebil --typ jbb --app testapps/dynTest.gnu
pebil --lib lib --typ ide src/pebil
